1. #include <stdio.h> is a header file library for input/output functions
2. int variable so the whole number that was given can be identified
3. printf function to show where the user will enter a number and to show the results
4. scanf function to read and identify if the number that was given is even or odd
5. if/else condition was added in case the given number is not even, it will be considered odd
6. the text inside the if condition (num % 2 == 0) shows what is considered even
7. %d refers to the integers
8. return 0 to end the function